  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from six experimental runs clustered near the nominal operating point (4.5 L/min, 3000 RPM); the decision record generalizes these results to the full intended operating envelope (2–7 L/min, 1500–4500 RPM) without statistical coverage analysis.",
